/Scac - who finds EQ dull nowadays..AO deadly dull and DAoC passable.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uswipey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swipey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 11:45:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Call of Cthulhu!?</span><hr size=1> Ah, dont knock AD&amp;D too hard.  At least it was fast to learn and fast to play.  Some other games out there any sort of combat resolution can take a half an hour <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sneekitwohands>Sneeki Twohands</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 2:43:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Call of Cthulhu!?</span><hr size=1> Yeh the AD&amp;D system was quick compared some of the others. One thing that would have made EQ a little more fun would be if mobs actually used bows, and they did decent damage. <br>
<br>
Imagine if in the orc camps that only the melees came out to melee, while a 3 or 4 bowmen and casters stayed behind to nuke everyone down from a distance (right now casters nuke as they get into melee range and nuke while in melee range, imagine if they never came in to melee). Then bows would be somewhat viable, if you didnt have a caster in your party. Bows would have to be fairly powerful, almost like caster nukes though (bowman criticals that hit often, and maybe have it so you could double attack with bow or even triple sometimes).<br>
<br>
I think DAOC does have the right idea about PVP. In the game you can have full blown pvp when you want to. They are lacking in the PVE department right now though. They just need to expand some and add more content then it would be very good game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uarafain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arafain</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/23/01 3:51:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wootage1.homestead.com/files/aoshi2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Call of Cthulhu!?</span><hr size=1> it's more a side-effect of game design than anything else.  As someone said before, why would a wizard in EQ stay back casting if he hits just as hard as a warrior does?<br>
<br>
That's one of the more sizable mistakes EQ made - giving all types of monsters the ability to hit just as hard.  Things would be a lot more interesting if caster mobs didn't hit hard at all, if archer mobs did good damage with bows but were weaker in melee combat, and disarmed mobs became very weak.<br>
<br>
It just plain doesn't make any sense for joe schmoe on the street in Qeynos to be able to punch me for 152 dmg a hit unless he's a monk.  If he's not, it's dumb.<br>
<br>
EQ is a very well-designed game in a lot of respects, and the fact that it's still fun to play three years after its release speaks volumes about its quality.  But whenever I'm given the option to either have a night playing D&amp;D 3rd ed. with my friends versus playing EQ, it's D&amp;D hands down every time.<br>
<br>
As far as enforced PvP, i LIKE PvP.  I look forward with great anticipation to games like Shadowbane, because PvP adds a huge dimension to the game.  However, the basic groundwork of the game still has to be okay - which, to me, is lacking in DAoC.  Anytime you are not rewarded for killing an enemy player in much the same manner as you'd be rewarded for killing an enemy monster, PvP will almost always be regarded as a waste of time - time spent that you could be using to level, and get more powerful in PvP.  PvP itself is often seen as a distraction to PvP.<br>
<br>
Furthermore....who cares whether or not game A unseats game B and steals all their clientele?  F that.  You find a game you like, Play it, have a great time.  But for heaven's sake, don't try to intrude your desires on people who are happily playing game A.<br>
<br>
&quot;Game A sucks!  Everybody come play game B, it's so much better!  That'll show those jerks who made game A!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Uh, I like game A fine, thanks.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;WTF!  Sycophant!  Infidel!  You'll betray us all, you groveler!&quot;<br>
<br>
Had enough of that, thanks. <p><b> -- Baron Arafain Entreri, 60 Assassin<br> -- Arafein Soulstriker, 53 Champion...err, 52, die Vox!<br> -- Arafax Kokorozan, 20 Monk Giantfriend<br> -- Requiem of Souls<br> -- Formerly of The Rathe Server, now of Zebuxoruk<br></b><i>"Once, in the old west, a gentleman shot a professional gunfighter in the back. When asked why he didn't give the other chap a chance to draw, he replied, 'Well, he's dead and I'm alive and that's how I wanted it to be." -- from <u>Red Planet</u>, Robert A. Heinlein</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessage?topicID=21353.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showMessage?topicID=21397.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=21244.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=21244.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21244.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=21244.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method